Sentencas: The BaCe0.5Fe0.5O3-delta (BCF) cathode consists of the ion-electron mixed conducting phase BaCe0.15Fe0.85O3-delta(BCF1585) and the proton-conducting phase BaCe0.85Fe0.15O3-delta (BCF8515).
Titulo: Tailoring the electrochemical reduction kinetics of dual-phase BaCe0.5Fe0.5O3-δ cathode via incorporating Mo for IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: In this paper, the electrochemical performance is improved by incorporating the high valence element Mo into the BCF and applied to intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs).
Titulo: Tailoring the electrochemical reduction kinetics of dual-phase BaCe0.5Fe0.5O3-δ cathode via incorporating Mo for IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: High-temperature X-ray diffraction (HT-XRD) and O-2-temperature programmed desorption (O-2-TPD) results show that Mo doping enhances the structural stability of BCF.
Titulo: Tailoring the electrochemical reduction kinetics of dual-phase BaCe0.5Fe0.5O3-δ cathode via incorporating Mo for IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: The X-ray photoelectron spectroscopy (XPS) results suggest that the introduction of Mo increases the amount of adsorbed oxygen and thus the oxygen reduction reaction (ORR) catalytic activity.
Titulo: Tailoring the electrochemical reduction kinetics of dual-phase BaCe0.5Fe0.5O3-δ cathode via incorporating Mo for IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: Compared to BCF, the polarization impedance of BaCe0.5Fe0.45Mo0.05O3-delta (BCFM) at 800.C is 0.154 Omega center dot cm(2), a reduction of 22 %.
Titulo: Tailoring the electrochemical reduction kinetics of dual-phase BaCe0.5Fe0.5O3-δ cathode via incorporating Mo for IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: Meanwhile, the BCFM output power at 800 degrees C is 778.01 mW center dot cm(-2), an improvement of 32.17 %, and maintains a stable current density after 250 h at 0.7 V.
Titulo: Tailoring the electrochemical reduction kinetics of dual-phase BaCe0.5Fe0.5O3-δ cathode via incorporating Mo for IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: The results demonstrate that Mo doping is an effective strategy to enhance the electrochemical performance of BCF.
Titulo: Tailoring the electrochemical reduction kinetics of dual-phase BaCe0.5Fe0.5O3-δ cathode via incorporating Mo for IT-SOFCs
